('15123', '20180709238', 5, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-08', 'This is my first time reviewing Phoenix, but I‚Äôve used up full bottles! It was a game-changer for me. I‚Äôve lived several places with different climates, yet it‚Äôs still performed well regardless.I have combination, sensitive skin that‚Äôs sometimes prone to hormonal acne near my jaw. (I used Accutane as a teen, so maybe this will be a helpful review for some of you.) Some popular ingredients will make me too oily and shiny at the drop of a hat... that includes hyaluronic acid, many peptides, and some silicones. Phoenix seems to calm and balance my face while tending to tone issues and small fine lines. Although I‚Äôm in my early 30s, I don‚Äôt use retinols... I do, though, pair this with the Sephora bakuchiol serum, which has a good effect. (Bakuchiol first, then this as a moisturizer.)Finally, I only use Phoenix at night unless my skin is feeling dry, but the effects are still noticeable and make me happy. I can‚Äôt say I have problems with it turning either me or random things orange, but it‚Äôs possible that could happen if you use too much? I only use four or five drops at a time, or occasionally less.To be honest, this may be the most worthwhile thing the company makes. :) I think it‚Äôs good value for money, personally, and while I‚Äôve tried to dupe it, I haven‚Äôt quite succeeded. Something about the ratio of ingredients suits me too well to be duplicated.', 'A forever fave', 'light', 'hazel', 'combination', 'blonde', 'P400204', 'Phoenix Rosehip Anti-Aging Face Oil - For Dry Skin', 'Herbivore', 88),
