('168780', '1760706321', 5, 't', 0.75, 12, 3, 9, '2022-12-15', 'I‚Äôm on my fourth jar of this and I‚Äôm REALLY hoping they never discontinue anything from the line.  For reference, I‚Äôm 38, avoid the sun when I can, and wear sunscreen when I can‚Äôt.  I‚Äôd say whatever fine lines I do have are about average for someone my age with a healthy skincare regimen.That said, this stuff is that miracle cream everyone talks about.  I use this in conjunction with the rest of the collection, but this immediately reduces any ‚Äúimperfections‚Äú and gone lines.  Not to mention it just makes my face look lifter, more plump, and glowy.  I get more compliments on my skin now when I don‚Äôt wear makeup (my makeup is intensely minimal, as it is).  I have strangers straight up tell me my skin looks incredible.The trick to this is the seasoning method: you can always add more, but you can never take it out.  In the morning, I simply add a small dot to the quadrants of my face and neck, then gently pat and massage it in.  I only add more of I feel areas need it.  Like a pea sized amount is more than enough.  At night, I‚Äôm a little more gracious with it for obvious reasons.One thing I do need to say is that Dior products are historically heavily scented.  I really don‚Äôt mind the scent at all.  In fact, I‚Äôve come to enjoy the signature fragrances of Dior skincare.  If you don‚Äôt like fragrance skincare, Dior is probably not the brand you should splurge on.  If you‚Äôre like me, trust that this will be a cream you‚Äôll be sorry you didn‚Äôt buy sooner.', '', 'light', 'brown', 'oily', 'red', 'P454806', 'Capture Totale Firming & Wrinkle-Correcting Cream', 'Dior', 130),
('168781', '11024401671', 5, 't', 0.5, 4, 2, 2, '2022-12-03', 'Only one. day 2 with the serum and cream and my sensitive skin is already glowing...will review back after a week but right now I‚Äôm very pleased.', 'Day 2 and my skin is glowing ‚ú®Ô∏è', 'light', 'green', 'normal', 'blonde', 'P454806', 'Capture Totale Firming & Wrinkle-Correcting Cream', 'Dior', 130),
('168782', '5333172484', 3, 'f', 0.3000000119209289, 10, 7, 3, '2022-11-28', 'I got a sample of this and a sample of the NuFace creams. They are quite different from each other, so not exactly comparing apples to apples. The Dior cream was much more intense. I felt sharp tingling to light burning sensations for a few minutes - but I will say the blemishes cleared up overnight with this product! A sample was not enough to confirm the firming/anti-aging claims. With the overnight results on blemishes, I was impressed. I ended up buying the full size NuFace instead for these reasons: much lower price mark (obviously) and far more gentle on the skin (no burning) with same blemish-clearing results. I‚Äôd like to try a couple full size bottles of the Dior since I‚Äôm really looking for firming (something NuFace didn‚Äôt live up to) but I don‚Äôt think the price mark is worth the disappointment expressed by others.', 'An investment which may or may not be worth it', 'light', 'brown', 'combination', NULL, 'P454806', 'Capture Totale Firming & Wrinkle-Correcting Cream', 'Dior', 130),
