('20234', '1410923063', 3, 'f', 0.7142860293388367, 7, 2, 5, '2021-10-11', 'This cream clogged my pores, leaving sprays of white heads across my cheeks and forehead‚Äîand you can see my other reviews to know that I‚Äôm now in my mid-30s with no issues with acne (teen or adult). I was gifted this in PR, and happy I never spent $120 on this cream. A reviewer below had the same concerns as I did: the great ‚Äúactives‚Äú like HA or Peptides are very low on the ingredient list, where as dimethicone (a silicone) is the 3rd. That‚Äôs is likely causing my clogged pores.Similarly, there‚Äôs a very strong fragrance. To me, it smells like papaya, which is nice! but I really dislike heavy fragrance so close to my eyes and nose. I can see why this is in the luxury skincare category‚Äîthe packaging is particularly excellent‚Äîbut this is not a luxury skincare product, unfortunately.  This actually feels a bit like a fashion house‚Äôs skincare brand, which haven‚Äôt we all learned by now is more marketing than materials?', 'Be Wary', 'light', 'blue', 'dry', 'blonde', 'P469112', 'KateCeuticals Total Repair Cream', 'Kate Somerville', 140),
('20235', '778569912', 2, 'f', 0.8333330154418945, 6, 1, 5, '2021-09-08', 'I received this product for review, and I was curious to try a product that promised ‚Äúyou‚Äôll see improved skin texture & firmness with diminished fine lines & wrinkles in just one week,‚Äú since most products take a long time to show their effects (weeks or months). I do see some smoothing, but it‚Äôs gone when I wash this cream off my face.Note that it has a VERY strong fragrance that lingers, even after you wash it off. I really hated the fragrance, so much so that I couldn‚Äôt wear this for more than an hour or two before running to double-wash my face. So I can‚Äôt speak to the long-term results you might get if you tolerate the smell and texture, only the first couple of hours of wear at morning and night.I assume the wash-off results are because it‚Äôs relying on dimethicone as the 3rd ingredient, per their website: ‚ÄúAqua/Water/Eau, Cetearyl Alcohol, Dimethicone...‚Äú The hyaluronic acid doesn‚Äôt show up until halfway down the ingredients list, as Sodium Hyaluronate. I‚Äôm guessing the peptide complex would be the various oils they list, also halfway down the ingredients list. In any case, these are in pretty small concentrations based on their positioning.But what about results? This cream goes on smoothly, but it leaves my face feeling slick like a silicone primer does. It sort of soaks in over several minutes, but not fast enough that I feel like my pillow case is safe. Nor does it really work well with makeup (oddly, since silicone primers usually work for me).Overall, there are far better products in this price range (and cheaper). This is one of my least favorite I‚Äôve ever tested, due to the smell and slick texture.', 'VERY strong fragrance, slick texture', 'fair', 'blue', 'combination', 'blonde', 'P469112', 'KateCeuticals Total Repair Cream', 'Kate Somerville', 140),
