('48596', '2573725473', 5, 't', 1, 9, 0, 9, '2021-08-05', 'I adore this cleanser. Yes, I hate the price, but it lasts forever, doesn‚Äôt strip my crazy sensitive skin & prone to breakouts skin, but removes all my makeup thoroughly. I most often cleanse once, but a few times a week, I use for a double cleanse to first remove makeup & sunscreen & then to cleanse my skin. I cleanse first thing in the morning, after workouts & again at night if I‚Äôve reapplied sunscreen or makeup. I‚Äôve had this for 3 months & still have a lot left. It‚Äôs crazy expensive, but I suffer from Perioraldermatitis, hyperpigmentation, combination skin that will break out if any ingredients are comedogenic. My skin is a million times better since I‚Äôve used this. I was using Jan Marini, which was causing my barrier to thin away. I started using a few Dr. Sturm products - including her ridiculously expensive moisturizer (desperation from a really bad PD flare up), which I seriously love, but it‚Äôs too much money for constant use. I will buy the cleanser again b/c I haven‚Äôt seen another product as both gentle, non-drying- and yet effective that isn‚Äôt the same price. My skin is super balanced, not oily, but sensitive. I read every ingredient & don‚Äôt leave anything on my skin with coconut derivatives.', 'Great for sensitive, PD prone skin.', 'mediumTan', 'green', 'combination', 'brown', 'P448545', 'Darker Skin Tones Foam Cleanser', 'Dr. Barbara Sturm', 75),
('48597', '31138107836', 5, 't', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2021-05-04', 'I really love this product , is gently and don‚Äôt dry the skin , but works perfectly well cleaning I will buy it again for sure', '', 'medium', 'green', 'dry', 'black', 'P448545', 'Darker Skin Tones Foam Cleanser', 'Dr. Barbara Sturm', 75),
('48598', '2265044275', 5, 't', 0.800000011920929, 5, 1, 4, '2021-01-23', 'Cleanses my skin and removes makeup well. I have oily skin and a tendency for clogged pores, but this works well (in combo with drinking lots of water) especially with Foreo.', '', 'light', 'blue', 'combination', 'blonde', 'P448545', 'Darker Skin Tones Foam Cleanser', 'Dr. Barbara Sturm', 75),
('48599', '2332031512', 4, 't', 0.8888890147209167, 9, 1, 8, '2020-08-22', 'This has become my absolute must have. It leaves my skin smooth and refreshed and my breakouts have decreased dramatically. Yes it pricey ( which is why it‚Äôs 4 out of 5 stars), however the size is pretty large and it‚Äôs done wonders for my skin.', 'My must have', 'deep', 'brown', 'oily', 'black', 'P448545', 'Darker Skin Tones Foam Cleanser', 'Dr. Barbara Sturm', 75),
('48600', '6668442409', 5, 't', 0.7777780294418335, 9, 2, 7, '2020-08-11', 'I have been using this cleaner for 3 months I have seen drastic improvement to my skin , I have acne prone skin, now I hardly ever get pimples , and I don‚Äôt have to double cleanse . I use her entire line and it‚Äôs works for me . This is my first ever review on any product.', 'Game changer', 'tan', 'brown', 'oily', 'black', 'P448545', 'Darker Skin Tones Foam Cleanser', 'Dr. Barbara Sturm', 75),
('48602', '5141422304', 1, 'f', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2023-03-14', 'I received a sample of this and remembered liking it so when I recently ran out of my sunscreen I thought I would try it. It leaves a very white cast on my skin and I‚Äôm not super tan right now so anyone with a darker complexion would look very pasty. I thought I could work with it and just put make up over it anytime I wear it. But it looks AWFUL under my make up. It makes my skin look flaky and patchy. It‚Äôs bizarre, definitely returning.', 'Try something else', 'mediumTan', 'hazel', 'oily', 'brown', 'P482741', 'Urban Environment Oil-Free Mineral Sunscreen Broad-Spectrum SPF 42', 'Shiseido', 38),
('48603', '35239254617', 5, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-13', 'Sunscreen is a must every day a few times a day! This one is just perfect, it melts onto the skin, doesn‚Äôt feel greasy and no flash back!! This is one of my favorite sunscreens.', 'This is a must!!', 'lightMedium', 'brown', 'combination', 'brown', 'P482741', 'Urban Environment Oil-Free Mineral Sunscreen Broad-Spectrum SPF 42', 'Shiseido', 38),
('48604', '21290233677', 5, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-10', 'I fell in love with the original formula which is white and it works great on my tan skin as it brightens up my face eliminating the need for foundation or powder. Wish they kept the original rather than replacing it still this product feels amazing on my skin; it absorbs quickly and leaves a surface ready for foundation, or not.', '', NULL, 'brown', 'combination', NULL, 'P482741', 'Urban Environment Oil-Free Mineral Sunscreen Broad-Spectrum SPF 42', 'Shiseido', 38),
('48605', '25568871528', 3, 'f', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2022-01-24', 'The product itself is nice, like others have mentioned a little goes a long way. You wouldn‚Äôt want to use this every day but it‚Äôs a lovely scrub. However the whole experience of using the product is cheapened by the packaging. It doesn‚Äôt feel nice or high-end, which makes me wonder if what‚Äôs inside is nice? The sticker label was crooked, the jar is very thin and flimsy plastic. To open the seal on the top there was no tab to pull so I had to cut it with a knife and product was wasted. Given the price point the packaging should be nicer. Drugstore products feel higher end.I know this is a new line for her so hopefully she can find a nicer 2oz jar!', 'Dr. Lara, the packaging is AWFUL!', 'light', 'brown', 'combination', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48606', '1663883274', 3, 'f', 1, 5, 0, 5, '2021-12-03', 'I‚Äôve used dermalogica microfoliant for years in the morning and wanted something different. This seemed similar in price and in what it promises to do. In comparison, this one is pretty abrasive - definitely not something I‚Äôd be able to use every morning like I did w the dermalogica one. And also, it‚Äôs minor but the packaging is pretty disappointing considering this is part of a line that is at a higher price point. I also ordered the vitamin c so we‚Äôll see how the packaging is there. 3 stars because the product itself seems decent enough to keep and use.', 'just ok', 'mediumTan', 'brown', 'normal', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48607', '11549298983', 5, 't', 0.75, 4, 1, 3, '2021-05-27', 'I really like this exfoliator! I been using this product for about two weeks now, twice a week. My skin feels very soft after using it, and it looks brighter. I‚Äôm very happy with the results. Keep in mind little goes a long way with this product. If you use too much your face will be really red after.', 'Amazing!', 'medium', 'brown', 'combination', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48608', '1551884291', 5, 't', 0, 1, 1, 0, '2021-04-23', 'Wow. I just got to know of Dr. Lara Devgan and I must say, I am most impressed! I love this scrub, just after one use my skin felt clean, clear, and smooth. Incredible exfoliator for the skin! It‚Äôs on the pricey side, like the rest of her line, however this is a little more reasonable and I‚Äôm finding it ‚Äúworth‚Äù the investment.', 'Soft and Smooth skin just after one use!', 'medium', 'brown', 'combination', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48609', '2444641383', 5, 't', 0.5, 2, 1, 1, '2021-03-12', 'I absolutely LOVE this scrub!! For years, I didn‚Äôt use physical exfoliants because I was worried about the potential damage they would cause to my skin barrier. I ended up trying this one and immediately knew that that I did not need to worry about that. This scrub uses sugar cane to exfoliate so it is extremely gentle and non abrasive. It‚Äôs also made with green tea which helps soothes the skin. After using this scrub, my skin feels soft and fresh. An added bonus is that my skin is able to absorb other products better. Highly recommend!!', 'An incredibly gentle exfoliant', 'lightMedium', 'brown', 'dry', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48610', '6141041', 1, 'f', 0.5, 6, 3, 3, '2021-03-11', 'If you have any sensitivity at all stay far away from this scrub. I can‚Äôt imagine it being good for anyone‚Äôs skin. It is so abrasive. I used it once and will finish it up I guess on my feet or inner thighs. It has the scrubbing power of exfolikate (which I like occasionally) times ten. Hard pass.', 'Too abrasive', 'light', 'brown', 'oily', 'brown', 'P469121', 'Microdermabrasion Scrub', 'Dr. Lara Devgan Scientific Beauty', 65),
('48615', '6817423185', 5, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-20', 'The first time I used this I thought for sure I wasn‚Äôt going to like it. It felt sticky, but I had used too much. The second night, I dotted it on my face with less product and that did the trick. My face felt so nourished the next morning and not at all sticky. Glad I gave it a second chance!', 'Perfect night moisturizer', NULL, 'brown', 'combination', NULL, 'P500120', 'Nourishing Rich Moisturizer with Hyaluronic Acid', 'Community Sixty-Six', 25),
