('48630', '1329573266', 3, 'f', 0.6666669845581055, 12, 4, 8, '2019-11-04', 'They seem fairly effective in removing makeup, but the wipes are small, so I needed 2 of them to remove a full face of makeup. I took them on an 8 day vacation & had to run out to a store to buy more wipes.', '', 'light', 'hazel', 'combination', 'brown', 'P444237', 'Mini Cleansing Wipes - Coconut Water', 'SEPHORA COLLECTION', 3),
('486391', '37288895046', 4, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-14', 'I‚Äôm giving this a 4 star and saying I REALLY do love the product- it‚Äôs soothing, silky, light and made my skin so soft and hydrated. But I really want a product that is cruelty free AND affordable, and Lancome unfortunately isn‚Äôt. Maybe one day they‚Äôll change their practice..  but until then, I‚Äôll find something else that ticks all my boxes.', 'LOVE it but had to move on...', NULL, 'hazel', 'combination', 'auburn', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('486392', '11605346299', 5, 't', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2023-03-13', 'I have been using this for a few weeks now! Love the easy application! My skin feels immediately hydrated and the formula is light! A must for any aging woman!', '', NULL, 'hazel', 'dry', 'auburn', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('486393', '2070315635', 5, 't', 0.5, 2, 1, 1, '2023-03-09', 'I‚Äôve been using this serum on my oily skin day and night, for 2 months, and my skin is amazing!!!! There is a noticeable difference in the texture of my 55 year-old skin! I‚Äôm sold!', 'Changed from my old regimen!', 'dark', 'brown', 'oily', 'auburn', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('486394', '10412902688', 1, 'f', 1, 5, 0, 5, '2023-03-09', 'After using this product I‚Äôve noticed no difference and sadly it has broken my whole face out. I‚Äôve never had this much of my face break out before. Wish it worked for me :(', '', 'fairLight', 'blue', 'combination', 'brown', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('486395', '33886961687', 3, 'f', 0, 1, 1, 0, '2023-03-08', 'My mom has always told me that the best time to start preventing and treating wrinkles is when you‚Äôre still young. I have the beginnings of laugh lines so I was very excited when I got the offer to try out Lancome‚Äôs face serum for free. I‚Äôve always heard great things about Genifique. My first impression of the Genifique is that it goes on nice and smoothly. It doesn‚Äôt make your skin feel oily but instead gives it a nice hydrated feel. It‚Äôs a lightweight serum that would be especially perfect in the hot, humid Louisiana heat. Over the course of the week and a half that I used the Genifique I felt like for at least the time immediately after applying the serum it felt like my slight laugh lines were barely noticeable. I can‚Äôt say that I saw a huge difference but I really don‚Äôt have any wrinkles so it‚Äôs hard to speak to how well it diminishes the appearance of fine line and wrinkles. My mother is of a more mature age and says that she sees a noticeable difference in the appearance of her fine lines and wrinkles. I‚Äôd be willing to try the product out longer to see if I notice more of a difference. For someone my age and for the price I don‚Äôt think I would necessarily recommend this product unless the person has a big problem with fine lines and wrinkles. I‚Äôve used other serums that work just as well to leave my skin feeling moisturized and have a much lower price point.', 'Undecided if it''s worth the hype', 'deep', 'brown', 'oily', 'black', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('486396', '5955097108', 3, 't', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-07', 'First, I‚Äôll say that I don‚Äôt dislike this serum. I have supremely dry skin and typically use much thicker serums, but even with this product‚Äôs sort of light consistency I find it very moisturizing after cleansing. Not moisturizing enough to use alone for me, but I can tell it‚Äôs more than just glycerin in a bottle. It plays well under many of my go-to moisturizers (Farmacy‚Äôs Honey Halo, presently) and I‚Äôve never had a problem with it under makeup. I am currently experiencing skin texture/mild acne and I‚Äôm not blaming this product, but it didn‚Äôt do much to smooth texture flare-ups on my skin. Though, it is very good at keeping things moisturized, and the parts of my face that aren‚Äôt prone to redness/irritation/acne are doing FABULOSULY.I bought this on sale and have been using it for about 3 months. At first, I was using it both day and night, then I realized it had Vitamin C and it actually makes no sense to use at night, despite the instructions on the bottle. I didn‚Äôt notice a difference when I went down to once a day, and I am a bit peeved that Lancome suggests twice daily usage on such an expensive serum.  I don‚Äôt regret the purchase (especially at 50% off), but I don‚Äôt think I will buy it full-price when I run out at this point in my life. If my texture were due solely to signs of aging (fine-lines, sun damage) etc. I think I would definitely consider it as a highly moisturizing, non-irritating DAYTIME serum. I could totally see myself using this consistently in about 10-15 years, so I hope they don‚Äôt change the formulation AND I get a promotion :)', '3.5 stars...mostly due to price', 'medium', 'brown', 'dry', 'black', 'P379510', 'Advanced G√©nifique Radiance Boosting Face Serum', 'Lanc√¥me', 132),
('48692', '25229019838', 1, 'f', NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-19', 'It broke me out after a couple of uses (cystic acne all over my face).', '', 'olive', 'brown', 'combination', 'black', 'P504780', 'Super Glow Vitamin C Brightening Face Serum', 'Glossier', 29),
('48693', '1079300047', 1, 'f', 0.9230769872665404, 13, 1, 12, '2023-03-15', 'I love a vitamin C serum, and checked this out because Dr. Shereene Idriss mentioned it as one of the products she liked with a certain type of vitamin C (and I‚Äôd tried others she‚Äôd recommended, so why not add another to my shelf?) After being completely underwhelmed with the results, and seeing people complain about Glossier batch codes on items that were *just* being sold, I checked mine, and it was nearly six years old, from 2017. Vitamin C is not a wildly durable ingredient, the bottle isn‚Äôt terribly protective... I mean, if Glossier is having financial issues and they went to Sephora to sell off old stock, the batch code makes sense, but Sephora should know better and do better by their customers.', 'Why is Sephora selling a 6 y.o. bottle of this?', 'fair', 'hazel', 'combination', NULL, 'P504780', 'Super Glow Vitamin C Brightening Face Serum', 'Glossier', 29),
