('6871', '35024132150', 4, 't', 0.8888890147209167, 9, 1, 8, '2022-12-26', 'My skin looks very shiny, shiny as in like a healthy glow. Been using it for two months now, it lasts a long time. Doesn‚Äôt remove stubborn mascara or makeup very well, but is good as a double cleanser. I use this after I remove my makeup with ponds cold cream. It does have a scent, but it is because it‚Äôs made with a French milled soap kind of cleansing agent. Didn‚Äôt cause breakouts, did make my skin feel tight, but that went away with use. Overall, good double cleanser but nothing special, did like the glow it gave me though! And it lasts a very long time, very big bottle. Hope this helps!', 'Honest review', NULL, 'hazel', 'normal', 'blonde', 'P481972', 'La Mousse OFF/ON Foaming Face Cleanser', 'Dior', 50),
('6872', '2773698546', 5, 't', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2022-11-27', 'I use it as a second step cleanser for days when I need to take off my makeup. It foams up and cleans really well. My face feels super clean afterwards but a tiny bit tight so it‚Äôs not a ‚Äúgentle‚Äú type of cleanser. Not the tightest I‚Äôve been with some other cleansers though. It‚Äôs pricey but cleansers always seem to last pretty long for me. The only ‚Äúick‚Äú is the strong scent. As with all Dior skincare products, this cleanser is heavily fragranced. Definitely not light. I don‚Äôt mind it but it does come on a bit strong when applying. If you can‚Äôt deal with fragrance, this cleanser may not be for you.', 'Cleans well but it''s heavily fragranced', 'light', 'brown', 'dry', NULL, 'P481972', 'La Mousse OFF/ON Foaming Face Cleanser', 'Dior', 50),
