('90810', '24337390623', 1, 'f', 1, 2, 0, 2, '2023-03-16', 'I have combo skin, oily in the T-zone and dry on my cheeks. I‚Äôm 41 and while I don‚Äôt look it yet, I would like to keep it that way. I personally feel like I‚Äôm starting to look it faster and faster these days. I was looking for a product to help smooth fine lines and wrinkles, and of course slow the clock down as much as possible. Due to the rave reviews I have read about Sunday Riley, especially the Luna, I was excited to try all of her products. Around Christmas I purchased 2 of the ‚Äúgo to bed with me‚Äú sets. I felt like this was a good cost effective measure to get a real test run on the whole system (cleanser, essence, A+, 5 star, Luna, Good Genes and Ice). $200 later and a few months, I‚Äôm here to report that I‚Äôm not impressed. I‚Äôm not sure what the hype is about. I didn‚Äôt see any improvement from the A+, 5 star, Luna, Ice, or Good Genes. Maybe it is just not right for my skin but I honestly think whether it was ‚Äúright‚Äú for me or not, there should have been some effect or minor improvement. My only other complaint is about the Luna, it doesn‚Äôt soak in, you go to bed slimy. On the other hand, the two products I didn‚Äôt expect to really care about but ended up really liking are the essence (Pink Drink) and the cleanser (Ceramic Slip). Still, I don‚Äôt expect I will be purchasing them. It‚Äôs a consideration in the future. Right now I‚Äôm over Sunday Riley and will continue my search for my skincare unicorn.', 'Disappointed, not my unicorn, moving on.', 'light', 'brown', 'combination', 'blonde', 'P309308', 'Good Genes All-In-One AHA Lactic Acid Treatment', 'Sunday Riley', 122),
